<paragraph id="8BD4B83EFF9FFFAD40EE1272393A0FE1" blockId="14.[189,1400,337,1755]" box="[193,1399,873,900]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<keyLead id="309A1B0BFF9FFFAD40EE1272393A0FE1" box="[193,1399,873,900]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
– Erect clypeal setae black (
<figureCitation id="1350A4BBFF9FFFAD420212713ECA0FE6" box="[557,647,873,900]" captionStart="Figs 49–56. 49" captionStartId="41.[189,241,1843,1869]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-99@41.[189,1399,265,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figs 49–56. 49. Sphex fumicatus Christ, 1791, habitus of ♀. 50. S. lanatus Mocsáry, 1883, habitus of ♀. 51. S. rufinervis Pérez, 1895, habitus of ♂. 52. S. taschenbergi Magretti, 1884, habitus of ♀. 53. S. fumicatus, frontal view of ♀. 54. S. taschenbergi, frontal view of ♀. 55. Geographic distribution of S. lanatus (red), S. rufinervis (blue) and S. taschenbergi (yellow). 56. Geographic distribution of S. tomentosus Fabricius, 1787 (red) and S. torridus F. Smith, 1873 (blue)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6299458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6299458/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
